                        <p>“We want this to be a collaborative process, not just among the two of us, and other MS researchers, but among the MS patients themselves,” Hartsell said. “There are tons of questions that need to be answered, and we want to make sure that the data we’re collecting—the answers that we’re obtaining—are ones that are relevant to the people who have to contend with this condition every day.”&nbsp;</p>

